The paper presents a new algorithm for online learning of recurrent network models, which is a common topic in machine learning and neural networks research. The paper also discusses the properties of the algorithm and compares it to existing methods, which suggests that it could be relevant to several sub-fields within computer science. Based on this, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions using the algorithm for tasks such as image classification and natural language processing, which could suggest relevance to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) as well.
